Frequently Asked Questions


Whats the difference between CodeMates individual offerings (Free and Premium) vs. CodeMate for Education?
While CodeMates Free and Premium plans can provide a student or educator with their own CodeMate account, CodeMate for Education is an institutional license that provides access to all students and faculty.

Can everyone at my institution use Codemate?
A CodeMate for Education institution-wide license grants access to all students, faculty, and administrators at your institution.

Will CodeMate for Education do students work for them?
CodeMate for Education offers suggestions across code quality, modularity, time complexity, good practices, incorrect syntax, and more.

As an institution, opting into AI writing code assistance unlocks real-time support for students and faculty. Providing guidance at every step of the coding process, CodeMate empowers them to not only brainstorm effectively before writing code, but to revise their work efficientlyand learn while doing it.

At the heart of CodeMate's next-generation programming assistance lies our unwavering commitment to customer trust, with rigorous standards for enterprise data security, user privacy, and responsible AI development.

Our recent series of features designed for CodeMate focuses on amplifying student's thinking and learning, rather than replacing it. AI guideline reminders, suggested academic prompts, and output explanations introduce students to the effective and responsible use of AI, equipping them for a future that will increasingly rely on this technology.

Does CodeMate for Education work with LMS software (such as Blackboard, Canvas, and Moodle)?
Yes, CodeMate works where you work. CodeMates suggestions are available on all major web browsers(Google Chrome, Mozilla Firefox, Microsoft Edge, and Safari and on desktop apps with our CodeMate for Windows and Mac product offering.
